the square is a 2008 australian neo-noir thriller film directed by nash edgerton , written by his brother joel edgerton and matthew &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , and starring david roberts and claire van der boom . based upon an original idea by joel , the project was written and then shelved by the actor because he felt it was not strong enough . it was only made after his director brother nash read the script and convinced him it could be filmed as a thriller . the film premiered in competition at sydney film festival on 15 june 2008 and after that had a limited release in australia on 31 july 2008 , and was released in north america in 2010 by apparition .